OL,7,FHe said: "(Al Maamoury) has taken our
OL,8,Flives away. The pain and devastation
OL,9,Fas a father, a mother and a sister, we
OL,10,Fcant settle. We wake up and we're
OL,11,Fcalling for him.
OL,13,F"Al Maamoury has been given his
OL,14,Fsentence but we've got a life sentence
OL,15,Fand we have to deal with that now for
OL,16,Fwhatever time we have left."
OL,18,FDetective Sergeant Paul Hughes from
OL,19,Ftheir Serious Collison Investigation
OL,20,FUnit said: "The events and trauma of
OL,21,Fthat day will never go away.
